  "preflight": [
    {
      "op": "log",
      "note": "Start page is the Integrations hub (settings-integrations.html), which renders with its own minimal Settings sidebar (Close Settings / All Settings / Integrations / Diagnostics) and every connector card in main content \u2014 the three-way branch of step 1 (Help Desk & Support / Authentication & SSO / Accounting & Finance) is read from those live groups; no persisted-preference staging is required to show it. Navigation to System Users (step 8) uses the full Settings accordion reached via the Settings rail -> settings.html: the Users & Security group is expanded with an `unless: uAndSExpanded` guard so the op only ever OPENS it (never toggles it shut), then the in-view System Users link is clicked. The standalone Integrations link is pinned at the BOTTOM of that accordion; it stays in the 1080px viewport (y651 all-collapsed, y731 with only Users & Security open) and is used for the step-9 and step-12 returns. Probe-verified July 11 from CDP 9225: the accordion's default profile state is all-collapsed (Integrations at y651, Users & Security header at y413, both in view); the accordion state is shared/persisted across the profile, so during probing it was restored to all-collapsed. RESIDUAL: if a prior session leaves many groups above Users & Security expanded at record time, the Users & Security header or the Integrations link could be pushed below the fold and the corresponding click would abort the take (fail-safe, never faked) rather than mis-fire \u2014 re-collapse the settings accordion before recording if that occurs."
    }
  ],
